Place the salmon in a pan and cover it with water. Add the lemon slices and peppercorns and bring to the boil. Poach for 1 minute and turn off the heat.Remove the salmon and drain on kitchen paper.Meanwhile, add the leeks to a small pan and drizzle with the olive oil and vinegar. Cook over a low heat for ten minutes, until the leeks are tender and have lost their bitterness.Serve the leeks on a warm plate and top with the poached salmon.